<div class=3D"quote">
<dl><dd><span title=3D"Source:&nbsp;Wonderbook: Book of Spells">"<i>This an=
cient and mysterious charm conjures a magical guardian, a projection of all=
 your most positive feelings. The Patronus Charm is difficult, and many wit=
ches and wizards are unable to produce a full, corporeal Patronus, a guardi=
an which generally takes the shape of the animal with whom they share the d=
eepest affinity. You may suspect, but you will never truly know what form y=
our Patronus will take until you succeed in conjuring it.</i>"</span></dd>
<dd>=E2=80=94 <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Miranda_Goshaw=
k" title=3D"Miranda Goshawk">Miranda Goshawk</a>'s overview of the Patronus=
 Charm<sup class=3D"noprint"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki=
/Wonderbook:_Book_of_Spells" title=3D"Wonderbook: Book of Spells">[src]</a>=
</sup></dd>
<dd></dd></dl></div>
<p>The <b>Patronus Charm</b> (<i>Expecto Patronum</i>) was the most famous =
and one of the most powerful defensive <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fando=
m.com/wiki/Charm" title=3D"Charm">charms</a> known to <a href=3D"https://ha=
rrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Wizardkind" title=3D"Wizardkind">wizardkind</a>.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-PM_4-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypott=
er.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Reference 4=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup> It was an immensely complicated and extremely difficult <a hre=
f=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Spell" title=3D"Spell">spell</a> t=
hat channelled the caster's positive emotions into a powerful protection. W=
hen cast properly, it evoked a partially-tangible positive energy force kno=
wn as a <b>Patronus</b> (pl. <b>Patronuses</b>)<sup id=3D"cite_ref-AQ_5-0" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus=
_Charm#cite_note-AQ-5" aria-label=3D"Reference 5"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> or <b>spirit g=
uardian</b>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-JKR_3-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-JKR-3" aria-label=
=3D"Reference 3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup> It was the primary protection against <a href=
=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Dementor" title=3D"Dementor">Dement=
ors</a> and <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Lethifold" title=
=3D"Lethifold">Lethifolds</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FBR_6-0" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note=
-FBR-6" aria-label=3D"Reference 6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> against which there were no o=
ther defences.
</p><p>There were two types of Patronuses: the incorporeal variant, which t=
ook the form of a shapeless wave of mist, and the corporeal variant, which =
had a definite shape, taking on the form of the animal that the caster had =
the greatest affinity for. The incorporeal Patronus was weaker than its cor=
poreal counterpart, but the corporeal Patronus was more advanced and diffic=
ult.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-PM_4-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harr=
ypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Refere=
nce 4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]=
</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Some wizards, like <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Re=
mus_Lupin" title=3D"Remus Lupin">Remus Lupin</a> chose to cast incorporeal =
Patronuses, even if they were capable of a more powerful corporeal Patronus=
, as a way to prevent the Patronus animal from revealing their identity.<su=
p id=3D"cite_ref-POA12_1-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypot=
ter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-POA12-1" aria-label=3D"Referen=
ce 1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup>
</p>
