<div class=3D"incontent_leaderboard fandom-ad-wrapper"><fandom-ad id=3D"inc=
ontent_leaderboard_1"></fandom-ad></div><h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=
=3D"History">History</span><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw=
-editsection-bracket">[</span><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</spa=
n></span></h2>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Early_history">Early history</span><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>It is evident from old woodcuts and scrolls that the Patronus Charm had =
been used since ancient times. Therefore, it is unknown who created it, or =
when it was first invented.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-WB_7-0" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-WB-=
7" aria-label=3D"Reference 7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> However, use of the charm is attes=
ted in Greek antiquity, as ancient Greek wizard <a href=3D"https://harrypot=
ter.fandom.com/wiki/Andros_the_Invincible" title=3D"Andros the Invincible">=
Andros the Invincible</a> became famous for being able to summon a Patronus=
 the size of a giant.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-COSG_8-0" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-COSG-8"=
 aria-label=3D"Reference 8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The charm also has a long associatio=
n with those fighting for lofty or noble causes (those able to produce corp=
oreal Patronuses were often elected to high office within the <a href=3D"ht=
tps://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Wizengamot" title=3D"Wizengamot">Wizengam=
ot</a> and <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Ministry_of_Magic=
" title=3D"Ministry of Magic">Ministry of Magic</a>).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-PM=
_4-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Pa=
tronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Reference 4"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>According to legend, one of the most famous Patronuses of all time w=
as a lowly <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Mouse" title=3D"M=
ouse">mouse</a>, which belonged to a young wizard called <a href=3D"https:/=
/harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Illyius" title=3D"Illyius">Illyius</a>. Illyiu=
s cast the Patronus Charm when his village was being attacked by the Dark w=
izard <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Raczidian" title=3D"Ra=
czidian">Raczidian</a> and his army of <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fando=
m.com/wiki/Dementor" title=3D"Dementor">Dementors</a>. Despite the mouse's =
diminutive size, it shone with a brilliant light, bringing the Dementors to=
 a halt as it nimbly moved through the ranks of fleeing villagers.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-WB_7-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fan=
dom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-WB-7" aria-label=3D"Reference 7"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a>=
</sup> Enraged, Raczidian decided to enter the fray himself. He tried to su=
mmon a Patronus to ward off Illyius's mouse.
</p><p>However, Raczidian failed to remember that only the pure of heart co=
uld produce a Patronus. Thus, for the first time in history, it was reveale=
d what happened when a competent, but unworthy wizard or witch attempted th=
e spell. Maggots shot out of Raczidian's wand and quickly devoured him as t=
hey engulfed his entire body. The villagers then hailed Illyius as a hero.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-WB_7-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypott=
er.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-WB-7" aria-label=3D"Reference 7=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup>
</p>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Second_Wizarding_War">Second Wizardin=
g War</span><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">[</span><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<div class=3D"quote">
