ontent_leaderboard_3"></fandom-ad></div><h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=
=3D"Nature">Nature</span><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-e=
ditsection-bracket">[</span><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span>=
</span></h2>
<div class=3D"quote">
<dl><dd><span title=3D"Source:&nbsp;Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaba=
n">"<i>Well, when it works correctly, it conjures up a Patronus, which is a=
 kind of anti-Dementor =E2=80=94 a guardian which acts as a shield between =
you and the Dementor. The Patronus is a kind of positive force, a projectio=
n of the very things that the Dementor feeds upon =E2=80=94 hope, happiness=
, the desire to survive =E2=80=94 but it cannot feel despair, as real human=
s can, so the Dementors can't hurt it. But I must warn you, Harry, that the=
 Charm might be too advanced for you. Many qualified wizards have difficult=
y with it.</i>"</span></dd>
<dd>=E2=80=94 <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Remus_Lupin" t=
itle=3D"Remus Lupin">Remus Lupin</a> explaining to <a href=3D"https://harry=
potter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter" title=3D"Harry Potter">Harry Potter</a=
> the charm's nature<sup class=3D"noprint"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.f=
andom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_the_Prisoner_of_Azkaban" title=3D"Harry Pot=
ter and the Prisoner of Azkaban">[src]</a></sup></dd>
<dd></dd></dl></div>
<p>According to <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Charms_of=
_Defence_and_Deterrence" title=3D"Charms of Defence and Deterrence">Charms =
of Defence and Deterrence</a></i>, the masterwork of the great eighteenth-c=
entury researcher of Charms, <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki=
/Catullus_Spangle" title=3D"Catullus Spangle">Professor Catullus Spangle</a=
>, the Patronus represented that which was hidden, unknown but necessary wi=
thin the personality. When a human was confronted with inhuman evil, such a=
s the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Dementor" title=3D"Dem=
entor">Dementor</a>, they must draw upon resources they might never have ne=
eded otherwise, and the Patronus was the awakened secret self that lay dorm=
ant until needed, which must now be brought to light.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-PM=
_4-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Pa=
tronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Reference 4"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=20
</p><p>Corporeal Patronuses took the form of whatever animal the caster had=
 the greatest affinity for. It could take a form that its caster might not =
expect, animals for which they had never felt a particular affinity, or (in=
 rare cases) even recognised. Every Patronus was as unique as its creator, =
and even identical twins had been known to produce very different Patronuse=
s.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-PM_4-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harryp=
otter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Referenc=
e 4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup>
</p>
