s, a common form of Patronus</p> 		 	</figcaption> </figure>
<p>Dogs, cats, and horses were among the most common Patronuses when cast. =
Given these animals' long affinity with humans, it is perhaps unsurprising =
that humans would commonly have an affinity for them. Although it must be n=
oted that any corporeal Patronus was highly unusual.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-PM_=
4-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Pat=
ronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Reference 4"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The unusual <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Wizardkin=
d" title=3D"Wizardkind">witches and wizards</a> who produced a Patronus tha=
t took the form of their favourite animal was an indicator of obsession or =
eccentricity. Here was a wizard who may not have been able to hide their es=
sential self in common life, and may have paraded tendencies that others mi=
ght have preferred to conceal. Whatever the form of their Patronus, one wou=
ld be well-advised to show respect, and occasionally caution, towards a wit=
ch or wizard who produced the Patronus of their choice.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
PM_4-6" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/=
Patronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Reference 4"><span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>If they were not protecting anyone, Patronuses seemed to take on the=
 traits of the creature they resembled and generally followed their caster =
around. This made it unsure whether or not they were truly sentient. Harry'=
s Patronus was able to follow both oral and physical commands.
</p><p><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Remus_Lupin" title=3D=
"Remus Lupin">Remus Lupin</a> also owned a <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.f=
andom.com/wiki/Patronus_spellbook" title=3D"Patronus spellbook">spellbook</=
a> which detailed the casting of the Patronus Charm.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-POA=
G_27-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/=
Patronus_Charm#cite_note-POAG-27" aria-label=3D"Reference 27"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>27<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"incontent_leaderboard fandom-ad-wrapper"><fandom-ad id=3D"inc=
ontent_leaderboard_4"></fandom-ad></div><h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=
=3D"Casting">Casting</span><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw=
-editsection-bracket">[</span><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</spa=
n></span></h2>
<div class=3D"quote">
<dl><dd><span title=3D"Source:&nbsp;Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaba=
n"><b>Harry Potter</b>: "<i>And how do you conjure it?</i>"</span></dd>
<dd><b>Remus Lupin</b>: "<i>With an incantation, which will work only if yo=
u are concentrating, with all your might, on a single, very happy memory.</=
i>"</dd>
<dd>=E2=80=94 Discussion on how to conjure a Patronus<sup class=3D"noprint"=
><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_the_Prison=
er_of_Azkaban" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban">[src]</a>=
</sup></dd></dl>
</div>
<p>To successfully cast the spell, one began by mustering the happiest memo=
ry they could think of; the happier the memory, the better the charm would =
work.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-POA12_1-6" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-POA12-1" aria-label=3D=
"Reference 1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup> Alternatively, one could fantasise a scenario that=
 would act as a very happy memory, as Harry did for his <a href=3D"https://=
harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Defence_Against_the_Dark_Arts" title=3D"Defence=
 Against the Dark Arts">Defence Against the Dark Arts</a> <a href=3D"https:=
//harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Ordinary_Wizarding_Level" title=3D"Ordinary W=
izarding Level">O.W.L. exam</a>, which impressed his examiners.<sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-OOTP31_28-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fan=
dom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-OOTP31-28" aria-label=3D"Reference 28=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>28<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup> The next step was to begin drawing circles with their <a href=
=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Wand" title=3D"Wand">wand</a> so as=
 to <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Powering-up_spells" titl=
e=3D"Powering-up spells">increase the power</a> of their spell.<sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-WB_7-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.c=
om/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-WB-7" aria-label=3D"Reference 7"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> They then had to say the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/I=
ncantation" title=3D"Incantation">incantation</a>, <i>Expecto Patronum</i>;=
 the Patronus would come from the tip of the wand and could be directed tow=
ards a target by pointing one's wand at said target.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-OPf=
_29-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/P=
atronus_Charm#cite_note-OPf-29" aria-label=3D"Reference 29"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>29<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The vast majority of witches and wizards were unable to produce any =
form of Patronus, and to create even the weaker and less difficult incorpor=
eal variant was generally considered a mark of superior magical ability.<su=
p id=3D"cite_ref-PM_4-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter=
.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Reference 4">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup> <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Rubeus_Hagrid" ti=
tle=3D"Rubeus Hagrid">Rubeus Hagrid</a> was an example of a wizard who coul=
d not conjure any form of Patronus, as the charm was too difficult for him.=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-HagridTweet_30-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-HagridTweet-30" aria=
-label=3D"Reference 30"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>30<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Alternatively, <a href=3D"https://harr=
ypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Minerva_McGonagall" title=3D"Minerva McGonagall">Mi=
nerva McGonagall</a> was the only person seen to be able to produce three P=
atronuses at once.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-DH30_31-0" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-DH30-31" =
aria-label=3D"Reference 31"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>31<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Some witches and wizards may have been unable to produce a Patronus =
at all until they had undergone some kind of psychic shock.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-PM_4-8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/w=
iki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Reference 4"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
