/a></p> 		 	</figcaption> </figure>
<p>It was possible to disguise the form one's Patronus took, which was done=
 both by <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Severus_Snape" titl=
e=3D"Severus Snape">Severus Snape</a> to hide his <a href=3D"https://harryp=
otter.fandom.com/wiki/Love" title=3D"Love">love</a> for <a href=3D"https://=
harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Lily_Potter_(I)" title=3D"Lily Potter (I)">Lily=
 Evans</a>, and by <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Remus_Lup=
in" title=3D"Remus Lupin">Remus Lupin</a>, who felt it would give away his =
<a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Lycanthropy" title=3D"Lycant=
hropy">condition</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-PM_4-9" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" ari=
a-label=3D"Reference 4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Patronuses only remained active whilst the caster was focusing on th=
em.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-DH13_17-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://ha=
rrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-DH13-17" aria-label=3D"R=
eference 17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Although it was extremely hard to fully conjure a Patronus, in an <a=
 href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Alternate_reality" title=3D"Al=
ternate reality">alternate reality</a>, <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fand=
om.com/wiki/Fourth_year" title=3D"Fourth year">fourth-years</a> in <a href=
=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Defence_Against_the_Dark_Arts" titl=
e=3D"Defence Against the Dark Arts">Defence Against the Dark Arts</a> class=
 were tasked with casting this charm.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-CC211_32-0" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Char=
m#cite_note-CC211-32" aria-label=3D"Reference 32"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"incontent_leaderboard fandom-ad-wrapper"><fandom-ad id=3D"inc=
ontent_leaderboard_5"></fandom-ad></div><h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=
=3D"Difficulty">Difficulty</span><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">=
]</span></span></h2>
<div class=3D"quote">
<dl><dd><span title=3D"Source:&nbsp;Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaba=
n">"<i>That's very, </i>very<i> advanced magic.</i>"</span></dd>
<dd>=E2=80=94 The difficulty and complexity of the charm<sup class=3D"nopri=
nt"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_the_Pri=
soner_of_Azkaban" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban">[src]<=
/a></sup></dd>
<dd></dd></dl></div>
<p>The Patronus Charm was widely regarded as advanced magic, far beyond <a =
href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Nastily_Exhausting_Wizarding_Te=
st" title=3D"Nastily Exhausting Wizarding Test">N.E.W.T.</a>-level. It was =
very complex, and many qualified <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/=
wiki/Wizardkind" title=3D"Wizardkind">wizards</a> and witches had trouble w=
ith it.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-PM_4-10" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Re=
ference 4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup> Being able to cast a Patronus, whilst fighting Dement=
ors or not, was not required to <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/w=
iki/Graduation_ceremony" title=3D"Graduation ceremony">graduate</a> from <a=
 href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Hogwarts_School_of_Witchcraft_=
and_Wizardry" title=3D"Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry">Hogwarts=
</a>, so it was something that was only taught under special circumstances.=
 <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Amelia_Bones" title=3D"Amel=
ia Bones">Amelia Bones</a> and potential members of the <a href=3D"https://=
harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Dumbledore%27s_Army" title=3D"Dumbledore's Army=
">D.A.</a> were all very impressed when Harry Potter revealed that he could=
 cast not only a Patronus Charm but a corporeal one to boot, which was nota=
bly more difficult than casting an incorporeal one, from as early as his th=
ird Hogwarts school year. In fact, <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.co=
m/wiki/Harry_Potter" title=3D"Harry Potter">Harry Potter</a> was one of the=
 youngest known wizards able to cast a Patronus; he was taught how to do so=
 in early <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/1994" title=3D"199=
4">1994</a> at the age of thirteen by <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom=
.com/wiki/Remus_Lupin" title=3D"Remus Lupin">Remus Lupin</a>, who described=
 the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Charm" title=3D"Charm">=
charm</a> as "<i>ridiculously advanced</i>".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-POA12_1-7" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus=
_Charm#cite_note-POA12-1" aria-label=3D"Reference 1"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<figure class=3D"thumb mw-halign-left show-info-icon" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thu=
