>
<p>In a <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Dumbledore%27s_Army"=
 title=3D"Dumbledore's Army">Dumbledore's Army</a> lesson, Harry taught the=
 members how to use the charm. Some were even successful in casting a corpo=
real form, though Harry said this might be because there was no <a href=3D"=
https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Dementor" title=3D"Dementor">Dementor</=
a> to make them frightened and thus impede their efforts.<sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-OOTP27_16-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.co=
m/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-OOTP27-16" aria-label=3D"Reference 16"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup> However, three members were later able to cast corporeal Patronuses=
 in the presence of Dementors.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-DH32_18-1" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_no=
te-DH32-18" aria-label=3D"Reference 18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>18<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Given that the success of the charm was directly reliant on the cast=
er retaining a particular mental state, it was more difficult to cast in em=
otionally trying circumstances. For instance, Harry Potter, Ron Weasley, an=
d Hermione Granger all had difficulty casting their Patronuses when under t=
he negative influence of <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Sly=
therin%27s_Locket" title=3D"Slytherin's Locket">Slytherin's Locket</a>, one=
 of <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Tom_Riddle" title=3D"Tom=
 Riddle">Lord Voldemort</a>'s <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wik=
i/Horcrux" title=3D"Horcrux">Horcruxes</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-DH15_33-0" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_=
Charm#cite_note-DH15-33" aria-label=3D"Reference 33"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>33<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and after =
witnessing the death of <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Fred=
_Weasley" title=3D"Fred Weasley">Fred Weasley</a> in the final <a href=3D"h=
ttps://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Battle_of_Hogwarts" title=3D"Battle of H=
ogwarts">battle</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-DH32_18-2" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-DH32-18=
" aria-label=3D"Reference 18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>18<span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> This feature of the Charm was par=
ticularly unfortunate, since the Charm's primary use was to defend against =
<a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Dementor" title=3D"Dementor"=
>Dementors</a>, which were specifically equipped to mentally unhinge people=
.
</p><p>Self-confidence may also play an important role in casting the spell=
. In 1994, after going <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Time-=
Turner" title=3D"Time-Turner">back in time</a>, Harry was able to cast the =
