<p>It was a general (and justified) belief held by the <a href=3D"https://h=
arrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Wizarding_world" title=3D"Wizarding world">wizar=
ding world</a> that only those who were pure of heart were able to cast the=
 Patronus Charm. This, however, was untrue, as several characters with nega=
tive personality traits were able to cast a fully-fledged Patronus.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-PM_4-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fa=
ndom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Reference 4"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup>
</p><p>If an unworthy witch or wizard attempted to cast it, they would be d=
evoured by a swarm of <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Maggot=
" title=3D"Maggot">maggots</a> coming from their <a href=3D"https://harrypo=
tter.fandom.com/wiki/Wand" title=3D"Wand">wand</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-WB_7=
-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patr=
onus_Charm#cite_note-WB-7" aria-label=3D"Reference 7"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> This could=
 be a metaphor for situations where individuals with certain psychological =
problems would feel discomfort from positive feelings like happiness or hop=
e, and might even crack up in such cases. However, Dark witches and wizards=
 would generally not try to produce a Patronus at all, not having any need =
for one. Most such men and women, who became desensitised to the effects of=
 the Dark creatures whom they may ally themselves with, regarded the Patron=
us not being necessary to know. <sup id=3D"cite_ref-PM_4-12" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_no=
te-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Reference 4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> For this reason, <a href=3D"=
https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Tom_Riddle" title=3D"Tom Riddle">Lord V=
oldemort</a> and his <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Death_E=
aters" title=3D"Death Eaters">Death Eaters</a> were not able to cast a Patr=
onus Charm (not that it was necessary, as they already had the Dark creatur=
es under their control via their affinity to darkness, and would have no us=
e for Patronuses).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-accio-quote_34-0" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-ac=
cio-quote-34" aria-label=3D"Reference 34"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>34<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"https://ha=
rrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Draco_Malfoy" title=3D"Draco Malfoy">Draco Malfoy=
</a> numbered among those unable to cast the Patronus Charm.<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-35" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki=
/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-35" aria-label=3D"Reference 35"><span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">[</span>35<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup i=
d=3D"cite_ref-LEGOY2_36-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypott=
er.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-LEGOY2-36" aria-label=3D"Refere=
nce 36"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>36<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Severus_=
Snape" title=3D"Severus Snape">Severus Snape</a> was the only Death Eater c=
apable of casting the charm.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-DH33_19-1" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note=
-DH33-19" aria-label=3D"Reference 19"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>However, some witches and wizards of questionable morals, such as <a=
 href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Dolores_Umbridge" title=3D"Dol=
ores Umbridge">Dolores Umbridge</a>, were able to produce corporeal Patronu=
ses. This may have been because she had a true and confident (though errone=
ous) belief in the righteousness of her actions.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-PM_4-13=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patron=
us_Charm#cite_note-PM-4" aria-label=3D"Reference 4"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-DH13_17-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom=
.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-DH13-17" aria-label=3D"Reference 17"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup> <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Merula_Snyde" title=
=3D"Merula Snyde">Merula Snyde</a> could only conjure an incorporeal Patron=
us, though it should be noted that she was only a fourth-year at the time a=
nd it was an advanced spell; the only other wizards known to produce a corp=
oreal Patronus by that age were <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/w=
iki/Harry_Potter" title=3D"Harry Potter">Harry Potter</a>, <a href=3D"https=
://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Nymphadora_Tonks" title=3D"Nymphadora Tonks"=
>Nymphadora Tonks</a>, and <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/J=
acob%27s_sibling" title=3D"Jacob's sibling">Jacob's sibling</a>.<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-HM4_37-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fando=
m.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-HM4-37" aria-label=3D"Reference 37"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>37<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup> <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patricia_Rakepick" =
title=3D"Patricia Rakepick">Patricia Rakepick</a> was a <a href=3D"https://=
harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Dark_wizard" title=3D"Dark wizard">Dark witch</=
a> who sadistically tortured Merula Snyde with the <a href=3D"https://harry=
potter.fandom.com/wiki/Cruciatus_Curse" title=3D"Cruciatus Curse">Cruciatus=
 Curse</a> and murdered <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Rowa=
n_Khanna" title=3D"Rowan Khanna">Rowan Khanna</a> with the <a href=3D"https=
://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Killing_Curse" title=3D"Killing Curse">Killi=
ng Curse</a>, yet was able to cast a corporeal Patronus in the form of a <a=
 href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Lion" title=3D"Lion">lioness</=
a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-HM618_38-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://h=
arrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-HM618-38" aria-label=3D=
"Reference 38"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>38<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"incontent_leaderboard fandom-ad-wrapper"><fandom-ad id=3D"inc=
