or Horcruxes</p> 		 	</figcaption> </figure>
<p>The other use was devised by <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/w=
iki/Albus_Dumbledore" title=3D"Albus Dumbledore">Albus Dumbledore</a>, who =
invented a way of using the Patronus (corporeal and incorporeal) as a means=
 of communication. They could deliver messages, speaking with the voice of =
the caster. This source of communication was believed to be exclusive to th=
e members of the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Order_of_th=
e_Phoenix" title=3D"Order of the Phoenix">Order of the Phoenix</a>. Using t=
he Patronus for communication offered great advantages in security, as Patr=
onuses identified the caster and were <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom=
.com/wiki/Dark_Arts" title=3D"Dark Arts">Dark Arts</a>-proof.<sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-JKR_3-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.co=
m/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-JKR-3" aria-label=3D"Reference 3"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> A prime example of this was when <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.co=
m/wiki/Minerva_McGonagall" title=3D"Minerva McGonagall">Minerva McGonagall<=
/a> used her <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Cat" title=3D"C=
at">cat</a> Patronus to call for help to the other <a href=3D"https://harry=
potter.fandom.com/wiki/Head_of_House" title=3D"Head of House">Heads of Hous=
es</a> in 1998, when she found out that <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fand=
om.com/wiki/Harry_Potter" title=3D"Harry Potter">Harry Potter</a> had retur=
ned to Hogwarts in search of <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki=
/Rowena_Ravenclaw" title=3D"Rowena Ravenclaw">Rowena Ravenclaw</a>'s <a hre=
f=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Ravenclaw%27s_Diadem" title=3D"Rav=
enclaw's Diadem">Diadem</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-DH30_31-2" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note=
-DH30-31" aria-label=3D"Reference 31"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
31<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Multiple Patronuses could be cast for communication, as McGonagall w=
as able to create three. Another was when <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fa=
ndom.com/wiki/Severus_Snape" title=3D"Severus Snape">Severus Snape</a> used=
 his Patronus to lead Harry Potter to a pool in the <a href=3D"https://harr=
ypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Forest_of_Dean" title=3D"Forest of Dean">Forest of =
Dean</a> in 1997, where he had laid the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fand=
om.com/wiki/Sword_of_Gryffindor" title=3D"Sword of Gryffindor">Sword of Gry=
ffindor</a> for Harry to retrieve. It is unknown if Snape had conjured the =
Patronus with instructions to follow, or if he was hiding nearby and contro=
lling it for this task.
</p>
