<ul><li>Two Patronuses planned for the films but were ultimately cut includ=
ed a <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Thestral" title=3D"Thes=
tral">Thestral</a> and a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/chimpanze=
e" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"wikipedia:chimpanzee">chimpanzee</a>.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-HPLE_50-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fan=
dom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-HPLE-50" aria-label=3D"Reference 50">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>50<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup></li>
<li>The Patronuses of <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/James_=
Potter_(I)" title=3D"James Potter (I)">James Potter</a> and <a href=3D"http=
s://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Minerva_McGonagall" title=3D"Minerva McGona=
gall">Minerva McGonagall</a> match their respective <a href=3D"https://harr=
ypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Animagus" title=3D"Animagus">Animagi</a> form. Thes=
e are the only characters whose Patronus and Animagus forms are known. Howe=
ver, not all Animagi have the same animal as their Patronus and Animagus.<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-51" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fa=
ndom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-51" aria-label=3D"Reference 51"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>51<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup>
<ul><li>Similarly, Remus Lupin's Patronus is a wolf, but whether this is un=
iversal among werewolves or not is unknown.</li></ul></li>
<li>In <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_t=
he_Prisoner_of_Azkaban" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban">=
Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban</a></i>, when Dementors attack Har=
ry, Hermione, and Sirius, Harry's Patronus is very weak and thin (based on =
the large amount of Dementors) yet the Dementors were still unable to pass =
through it. However, one Dementor made it vanish by gesturing at it.</li>
<li>In the first chapter of <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wi=
ki/Harry_Potter_and_the_Deathly_Hallows" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Deat=
hly Hallows">Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows</a></i>, a white peacock =
appears in the gardens of Malfoy Manor. Some fans believed this bird to be =
<a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Lucius_Malfoy" title=3D"Luci=
us Malfoy">Lucius Malfoy</a>'s Patronus. However, <a href=3D"https://harryp=
otter.fandom.com/wiki/J._K._Rowling" title=3D"J. K. Rowling">J. K. Rowling<=
/a> stated that no <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Death_Eat=
ers" title=3D"Death Eaters">Death Eater</a> except Severus Snape could (or =
had a need to) conjure a Patronus, because Death Eaters fight alongside tha=
t which Patronuses fight against.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-bloomsbury_52-0" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Char=
m#cite_note-bloomsbury-52" aria-label=3D"Reference 52"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>52<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> This mea=
ns that the peacock was in fact a living creature. It is stated in <i><a hr=
ef=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_the_Deathly_Hall=
ows" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows">Harry Potter and the De=
athly Hallows</a></i> that the creature was in fact an albino peacock.</li>
<li>In the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_=
the_Prisoner_of_Azkaban_(video_game)" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Prisone=
r of Azkaban (video game)">video game adaptation</a> of <i><a href=3D"https=
://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_the_Prisoner_of_Azkaban" ti=
tle=3D"Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban">Harry Potter and the Priso=
ner of Azkaban</a></i>, the more moderate <i>Expecto Patronum</i> is a ball=
 of light.
<ul><li>In the console versions, it works as a guided-missile that can only=
 be steered left or right, and accelerate.</li>
<li>In the PC version, before being cast, a white ring goes up Harry's arm =
and if it reaches the top of the wand, Harry has to try the spell again, an=
d it is used only to attack Dementors (it also produces lightning effects).=
 At the climax of the game, a stag (Harry's Patronus) jumps out of the wand=
 to drive away all the Dementors nearby attacking Harry and Sirius, and its=
 during that battle in the console versions, Harry's Patronus changes into =
a stag with altered controls.</li></ul></li>
<li>In said video game, the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/=
Harry_Potter_and_the_Deathly_Hallows:_Part_1_(video_game)" title=3D"Harry P=
otter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 1 (video game)">first video game adapti=
on</a> of <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_an=
d_the_Deathly_Hallows" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows">Harry=
 Potter and the Deathly Hallows</a></i>, and <i><a href=3D"https://harrypot=
ter.fandom.com/wiki/LEGO_Harry_Potter:_Years_1-4" title=3D"LEGO Harry Potte=
r: Years 1-4">LEGO Harry Potter: Years 1-4</a></i>/<i><a href=3D"https://ha=
rrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/LEGO_Harry_Potter:_Years_5-7" title=3D"LEGO Harry=
 Potter: Years 5-7">LEGO Harry Potter: Years 5-7</a></i>, the Patronus Char=
m appears to push the Dementors away with the first shot, and destroys them=
 with the second shot.</li>
<li>In <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/LEGO_Harry_Potter:_Ye=
ars_1-4" title=3D"LEGO Harry Potter: Years 1-4"><i>LEGO Harry Potter: Years=
 1-4</i></a>, only Harry can learn this spell due to Ron and Hermione havin=
g to chase <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Peter_Pettigrew" =
title=3D"Peter Pettigrew">Scabbers</a> and <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.f=
andom.com/wiki/Crookshanks" title=3D"Crookshanks">Crookshanks</a> before Lu=
pin can start the lesson. Instead, Ron and Hermione learn <i><a href=3D"htt=
ps://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Boggart-Banishing_Spell" title=3D"Boggart-=
Banishing Spell">Riddikulus</a></i>, which Harry does not get to learn. As =
Harry's <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Boggart" title=3D"Bo=
ggart">Boggart</a> is a <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Deme=
ntor" title=3D"Dementor">Dementor</a>, and due to him not having access to =
<i>Riddikulus</i>, this makes Harry the only character to have to use a dif=
ferent spell to defeat a Boggart.</li>
<li>The lecture that Harry gives on Patronuses to <a href=3D"https://harryp=
otter.fandom.com/wiki/Dumbledore%27s_Army" title=3D"Dumbledore's Army">Dumb=
ledore's Army</a> in the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Har=
ry_Potter_and_the_Order_of_the_Phoenix_(film)" title=3D"Harry Potter and th=
e Order of the Phoenix (film)">film adaptation</a> of <i><a href=3D"https:/=
/harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_the_Order_of_the_Phoenix" tit=
le=3D"Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix">Harry Potter and the Order=
 of the Phoenix</a></i> is extremely similar to the lecture <a href=3D"http=
s://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Remus_Lupin" title=3D"Remus Lupin">Remus Lu=
pin</a> gave him in the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harr=
y_Potter_and_the_Prisoner_of_Azkaban_(film)" title=3D"Harry Potter and the =
Prisoner of Azkaban (film)">film adaptation</a> of <i><a href=3D"https://ha=
rrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_the_Prisoner_of_Azkaban" title=
=3D"Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban">Harry Potter and the Prisoner=
 of Azkaban</a></i>.</li>
<li>In <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_t=
he_Deathly_Hallows:_Part_1" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: =
Part 1">Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 1</a></i>, <a href=3D"ht=
tps://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Dolores_Umbridge" title=3D"Dolores Umbrid=
ge">Dolores Umbridge</a>'s Patronus seems to emanate a shield that keeps th=
e Dementors separated from everyone in the courtroom. In addition, Kingsley=
 Shacklebolt's Patronus is described in the novel as taking the form of a l=
ynx; however, in the film it is depicted as a shimmering comet of light fro=
m which springs silvery images of witches and wizards screaming in terror, =
as Kingsley's voice details the death of Scrimgeour and the fall of the Min=
istry.</li>
<li>In <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/LEGO_Harry_Potter:=
_Years_1-4" title=3D"LEGO Harry Potter: Years 1-4">LEGO Harry Potter: Years=
 1-4</a></i>, <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Tom_Riddle" ti=
tle=3D"Tom Riddle">Voldemort</a>, <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com=
/wiki/Lucius_Malfoy" title=3D"Lucius Malfoy">Lucius Malfoy</a>, <a href=3D"=
https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Walden_Macnair" title=3D"Walden Macnair=
">Walden Macnair</a>, <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Bartem=
ius_Crouch_Junior" title=3D"Bartemius Crouch Junior">Barty Crouch Jnr</a>, =
and an unnamed <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Death_Eaters"=
 title=3D"Death Eaters">Death Eater</a> can all cast the spell, despite the=
 fact that Rowling stated that no Death Eater besides Severus Snape could p=
roduce a Patronus. This was most likely incorporated for gameplay purposes.=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-53" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.=
fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-53" aria-label=3D"Reference 53"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>53<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup>
<ul><li>This was corrected in <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wik=
i/LEGO_Harry_Potter:_Years_5-7" title=3D"LEGO Harry Potter: Years 5-7"><i>Y=
ears 5-7</i></a>, where the aforementioned Death Eaters had <i>Expecto Patr=
onum</i> removed from their spell wheels, however Bellatrix could still use=
 it for some reason despite also being a Death Eater.</li></ul></li>
<li>According to <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Wizards%27_=
Ordinary_Magic_and_Basic_Aptitude_Test" title=3D"Wizards' Ordinary Magic an=
d Basic Aptitude Test">W.O.M.B.A.T.</a>, it is possible that Patronuses var=
y in strength according to which animal's form they take. Later canon from =
<i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Wonderbook:_Book_of_Spell=
s" title=3D"Wonderbook: Book of Spells">Wonderbook: Book of Spells</a></i>,=
 however, stresses that this is not the case and that the form of the anima=
l has no correlation to the strength of the Patronus (see, for instance, <a=
 href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Illyius" title=3D"Illyius">Ill=
yius</a> and <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Symposia_Rawle"=
 title=3D"Symposia Rawle">Symposia Rawle</a>).</li>
<li>J. K. Rowling stated that the happy memory that would produce the stron=
gest Patronus for her would be the births of any of her three children, tho=
ugh a close fourth would be when she learned that <i><a href=3D"https://har=
rypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_the_Philosopher%27s_Stone" title=
=3D"Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone">Harry Potter and the Philosop=
her's Stone</a></i> was going to be published.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-bluepeter=
_54-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/P=
atronus_Charm#cite_note-bluepeter-54" aria-label=3D"Reference 54"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>54<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p> She has also stated that she'd like for her Patronus to be an otter, lik=
e Hermione's, but she has a feeling it might actually be a large dog.<sup i=
d=3D"cite_ref-bloomsbury_52-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harry=
potter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-bloomsbury-52" aria-label=
=3D"Reference 52"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>52<span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">]</span></a></sup> However, in a message on <a href=3D"https://h=
arrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Twitter" title=3D"Twitter">Twitter</a> in <a hre=
f=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/2014" title=3D"2014">2014</a>, she=
 claimed it would be a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_pi=
ne_marten" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"wikipedia:European pine marten">pine ma=
rten</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-55" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://har=
rypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-55" aria-label=3D"Referen=
ce 55"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>55<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup> Additionally, in a 2000 interview, she stated that the P=
atronus Charm was her favourite spell in the series so far.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-AOLLive&quot;_56-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.=
fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-AOLLive%22-56" aria-label=3D"Refer=
ence 56"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>56<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup> Rowling later revealed that a pine marten was what she=
 had tested as in the initial form of the Patronus test that was later post=
ed on Pottermore. She took the test again in its final form and tested as a=
 heron.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-rowlingpottermorepatronus_57-0" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note=
-rowlingpottermorepatronus-57" aria-label=3D"Reference 57"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>57<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>Learning to cast a Patronus is one of the tasks given to the player in =
the final Chapter of the game <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/=
wiki/Wonderbook:_Book_of_Spells" title=3D"Wonderbook: Book of Spells">Wonde=
rbook: Book of Spells</a></i>. For learning the incantation and gesture, th=
e player is given the Trophy "Expecto Patronum!" On the next page, the play=
er is given the chance to cast a true Patronus, the form of which is appare=
ntly chosen randomly. Amongst the possible Patronuses are a bat, a bull, a =
cat, a goat, a horse, a rabbit, a scorpion and a snake.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
wbtruepatronus_58-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fan=
dom.com/wiki/Patronus_Charm#cite_note-wbtruepatronus-58" aria-label=3D"Refe=
rence 58"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>58<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup> For discovering their Patronus, the player is awarded=
 the Trophy "True Patronus."</li>
<li>J. K. Rowling has stated the only way that a Patronus is able to change=
 its current form is through eternal unchangeable love.</li>
<li>Although J. K. Rowling has stated that the plural form is Patronuses an=
d not Patroni, the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/German" t=
itle=3D"German">German</a> <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/H=
arry_Potter_in_translation" title=3D"Harry Potter in translation">translati=
on</a> always translates it as Patroni.</li>
<li>On <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/22_September" title=
=3D"22 September">22 September</a> <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.co=
m/wiki/2016" title=3D"2016">2016</a>, <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fan=
dom.com/wiki/Pottermore" title=3D"Pottermore">Pottermore</a></i> unveiled t=
he long-awaited and discussed option for members of the site to determine t=
heir patronus. This takes the form of a quiz of several questions that can =
only be taken once, at which point the member's Patronus is revealed and ad=
ded to their member profile.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-pottermorepatronus_59-0" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Patronus_C=
harm#cite_note-pottermorepatronus-59" aria-label=3D"Reference 59"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>59<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p></li>
<li>When <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/J._K._Rowling" titl=
e=3D"J. K. Rowling">J. K. Rowling</a> was asked about the form of <a href=
=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Newton_Scamander" title=3D"Newton S=
camander">Newton Scamander</a>'s Patronus, she said that it would be a spoi=
ler to future films of the Fantastic Beasts series.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Newt=
_60-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/P=
atronus_Charm#cite_note-Newt-60" aria-label=3D"Reference 60"><span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">[</span>60<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></l=
i>
<li>On <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Pottermore" title=
=3D"Pottermore">Pottermore</a></i> (and in other releases), a few animals s=
uch as horses, cats, squirrells and swans, have Patronuses in different hai=
r colours of the animal. It is unknown how hard the difference is to tell i=
n-universe, since all Patronuses are silver in colour, and therefore all lo=
ok the same (aside from their forms).</li></ul>
<div class=3D"incontent_leaderboard fandom-ad-wrapper"><fandom-ad id=3D"inc=
ontent_leaderboard_12"></fandom-ad></div><h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=
=3D"Patronuses_in_the_films">Patronuses in the films</span><span class=3D"m=
w-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li>In the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_=
and_the_Order_of_the_Phoenix_(film)" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Order of=
 the Phoenix (film)">film adaptation</a> of <i><a href=3D"https://harrypott=
er.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_the_Order_of_the_Phoenix" title=3D"Harr=
y Potter and the Order of the Phoenix">Harry Potter and the Order of the Ph=
oenix</a></i>, Harry's Patronus physically attacks the Dementors by chargin=
g at them, as depicted in the books, with the first successful patronus shi=
eld he conjured being used to force a <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom=
.com/wiki/Boggart" title=3D"Boggart">Boggart</a> in the form of a Dementor =
back into its trunk. Additionally, Patronuses produced by the members of Du=
mbledore's Army make noises and are capable of interacting with physical ob=
jects, such as Ron's dog Patronus knocking over <a href=3D"https://harrypot=
ter.fandom.com/wiki/Neville_Longbottom" title=3D"Neville Longbottom">Nevill=
e Longbottom</a>. In <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harr=
y_Potter_and_the_Deathly_Hallows:_Part_1" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Dea=
thly Hallows: Part 1">Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 1</a></i>,=
 Umbridge's Patronus was heard hissing.</li>
<li>There was a noted change in appearance of Patronuses in general in the =
<i>Order of the Phoenix</i> film. In films 5=E2=80=938, Patronuses appear t=
o be very wispy and airy, while in the third film they look more substantia=
l, solid and brighter.</li>
<li>In <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_t=
he_Deathly_Hallows:_Part_1" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: =
Part 1">Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 1</a></i>, during the <a=
 href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Infiltration_of_the_Ministry_o=
f_Magic" class=3D"mw-redirect mw-disambig" title=3D"Infiltration of the Min=
istry of Magic">infiltration of the Ministry of Magic</a>, Umbridge's Patro=
nus was very clearly seen several times in the same scene and often looked =
less like a cat and more like a reanimated, feline corpse, with the skeleta=
l features visible. This is odd for a Patronus, as they usually look quite =
'alive' and well, and its twisted form may be a nod to both Umbridge's natu=
re and the circumstances under which it was cast.</li>
<li>In the <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_=
the_Prisoner_of_Azkaban_(film)" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Prisoner of A=
zkaban (film)">film adaptation</a> of <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fan=
dom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_and_the_Prisoner_of_Azkaban" title=3D"Harry Potte=
r and the Prisoner of Azkaban">Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban</a>=
</i>, the Patronus in its powerful wave-like form emits a deep reverberatin=
g sound. In <i><a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Harry_Potter_=
and_the_Deathly_Hallows:_Part_2" title=3D"Harry Potter and the Deathly Hall=
ows: Part 2">Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2</a></i>, this eff=
ect was also used when <a href=3D"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Aberf=
orth_Dumbledore" title=3D"Aberforth Dumbledore">Aberforth Dumbledore</a> pr=
otected Hogwarts from Dementors.</li></ul>
